<h2>
    <a href="/blog/cobweb-plots/">Cobweb plots</a>
</h2>




<h6 class="post-meta">
    Posted by:
    
    <a href="/blog/author/christian/">christian</a>
    
    
    
    
    on 1 Nov 2017
</h6>





<a href="/blog/cobweb-plots/">
    <img class="img-thumbnail pull-left" src="/static/media/uploads/blog/cobweb/.thumbnails/cobweb_0.2_3.8.png/cobweb_0.2_3.8-90x90.png">
</a>





<p>A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cobweb_plot">cobweb plot</a> is often used to visulaize the behaviour of an <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Iterated_function">iterated function</a>. That is, the sequence of values obtained from setting $x_{n+1} = f(x_n)$, starting at some value $x_0$.</p>




<div class="blog-list-detail">
    
    
    <p>
    <a href="/blog/cobweb-plots/">read more</a>
    
    /
    
    <a href="/blog/cobweb-plots/#comments">
        4 comments
    </a>
    
    
    </p>
</div>




